glosses: to scatter; to disperse; to dispel; to dissipate
to distribute; to deal; to dole out, give out, hand out; to dispense
to mess up, disorder, put (something) into disarray, disarray
to cause (something) to break into pieces, cause (something) to disintegrate or spall off; to smash (something) to bits.

etymology: From Ottoman Turkish طاغتمق (dağıtmak). Apparently causative form of Proto-Turkic *dar- (“to go apart, scatter, spread”), however it displaced the original verb. The reason of -/r/- to -/ğ/- assimilation is unknown, see more at dağılmak.
